sentences: Charles Tolliver (born 1942) is an American jazz trumpeter, composer, and co-founder of Strata East Records.
Tolliver was born in Jacksonville, Florida, in 1942 and moved with his family to New York City when he was 10.
He came to prominence in 1964, playing and recording on Jackie McLean's Blue Note albums.
In 1971, Tolliver and Stanley Cowell founded Strata-East Records, and Tolliver released many albums and collaborations on Strata-East.
With Love was nominated in 2007 for a Grammy award for Best Large Jazz Ensemble.
1965: "Brilliant Corners" on The New Wave in Jazz (Impulse!)
1972: Live at the Loosdrecht Jazz Festival (Strata-East), also released as Grand Max (Black Lion)
1988: Live in Berlin at the Quasimodo Vol.

Serenade to a Soul Sister (Blue Note, 1968)With McCoy Tyner
Following a long hiatus, he reemerged in the late 2000s, releasing two albums arranged for big band, With Love and Emperor March.
Tolliver attended Howard University in the early 1960s as a pharmacy major, when he decided to pursue music as a career and return home to New York City.
